The paper also makes use of stateless oblivious RAM simulation, which is a technique commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of pseudorandom hash functions, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CR, cs.DS, and cs.DB, followed by cs.CC and cs.IT.
